Guodian Said to Seek Up to $643M in IPO

-- B y   F o x   H u
-- 
2011-12-05T04:13:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-05/guodian-said-to-seek-up-to-643m-in-ipo.html
Guodian Technology & Environment
Group Corp. , a Chinese maker of wind power equipment, is seeking
up to HK$5 billion ($643 million) in an initial public offering
in Hong Kong, according to two people familiar with the matter.  The Beijing-based unit of China Guodian Corp. plans to sell
2.08 billion shares for between HK$2.16 and HK$2.42 each, the
people said, asking not to be identified as the information is
private. Guodian Technology aims to start trading this month,
the people said.  Guodian Technology’s operating profit rose 93 percent to
496 million yuan ($78 million) in the six months ended June from
a year earlier, according to a  filing  to Hong Kong’s stock
exchange today. Revenue increased 84 percent to 6.8 billion yuan
in the same period, the filing shows.  Initial public offerings in  Hong Kong  have raised $16.2
billion this year, compared with $50.3 billion for the same
period last year, data compiled by Bloomberg show.  A spokesperson for Guodian Technology in Beijing was not
immediately available to comment on the IPO.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fox Hu in Hong Kong at 
